##State Grid Restarts "MONEY-LOSING" project in response to epidemic

Weixin caijingEleven

The function introduction by "CAIJING" Magazine Company Industry Report team to create, discuss the success or failure of the enterprise, explore the rise and fall of the industry, promote sunshine business

The pumped-storage hydroelectricity, a necessary source for regulating peak and trough power demand, was halted three months ago by the State Grid for failing to include transmission and distribution tariffs and for lack of a market based pricing mechanism

By Han Shulin

Editor | Marc

On the morning of February 18, Mao Weiming, chairman and secretary of the Leading Party Group of the State Grid Corporation of China, announced the start of construction of the pumped-storage hydroelectricity project in Yuanqu County, marking the full start of the project.

The function of the pumped-storage hydroelectricity is to regulate the peak load, that is, to make up for the shortage of other power sources during the peak hours.

The project is one of 12 measures taken by the State Grid on February 7 to respond to the impact of the epidemic and boost the resumption of production by enterprises.

The third of the 12 measures is to increase investment in new projects, such as the newly started 800 KV SHANBEI-WUHAN HVDC project and the Shanxi Yuanqu pumped-storage hydroelectricity project, with a total investment of 26.5 billion yuan.

Of the two new projects, reboot, the pumped storage plant, is a little different. Under the previous Chairman of State Grid, Kou Wei, in November 2019, the state grid once issued a strict regulation on grid investment, which proposed that investment in the grid should be determined by output and the scale of grid investment should be strictly controlled, and made it clear that no new pumped storage projects would be arranged to start.

On January 17,2020, the State Grid unexpectedly changed its commander in chief. The former chairman of the State Grid, Kou Wei, was transferred to Datang as general manager of the Power Generation Group, and the former vice governor of Jiangxi Province, Mao Weiming, was transferred to the State Grid as chairman, become the first State Grid non-power enterprise origin of the chairman.

In order to deal with the impact of the epidemic situation and promote the resumption of work and production, the state grid has restarted the construction of pumped storage power stations again after three months of suspension of the project.

The pumped storage project is located in Jieyu Township, Yuanqu County, Shanxi Province, with an installed capacity of 1.2 million kilowatts and four 300,000 kilowatts reversible pumped storage units, with a total investment of 7.96 billion yuan. December 16,2019 was approved by the Shanxi Provincial Development and Reform Commission, 2028 is expected to put into production power generation.

Information released by the State Grid shows that the project will directly drive upstream and downstream industries to resume production, increasing the output value of the power generation equipment manufacturing industry by about 2 billion yuan, and estimating that on average local financial revenue will increase by about 150 million yuan per year during the construction period, it provides 3,500 jobs of various types, and during the operation period, increases the annual revenue by about 110 million yuan, and promotes the development of other industries.

Before the construction of the new pumped storage power station, the original pumped storage project under construction has started to resume. February 14,15, the State Grid Xinyuan Company's pumped-storage hydroelectricity in Qingyuan Manchu Autonomous County, Hebei Province, Fengning Pumped Storage Power Station have resumed work.

The two projects, with a total investment of 30 billion yuan, will have an installed capacity of 1.8 and 3.6 gigawatts respectively, of which the Fengning Pumped Storage Power Station, with an installed capacity of 3.6 gigawatts, is currently the world's largest pumped storage plant. By the end of 2019, the pumped-storage power stations under construction and in operation in the state grid were 19.46 million kilowatts and 35.85 million kilowatts respectively.

The construction of pumped storage power station can increase the capacity of peak regulation of power system. In Shanxi, the power structure is dominated by thermal power, with the installed share reaching 72% , and the peak-to-valley load difference will further increase in the future. The construction of pumped storage power stations can be used to reduce peak load and fill valley, and alleviate peak regulation pressure, improving the economy, security and stability of power grid operation. The plant is designed to generate 1.2 billion kilowatt-hours of electricity a year and pump 1.6 billion kilowatt-hours of water annually, according to the State Grid.

However, for pumped-storage power stations, the lack of price mechanism, so that the recovery of investment has become the biggest difficulty, but also before the state grid called off the construction of pumped-storage power stations an important reason.

Previously pumped storage power stations were mainly invested by grid companies. But in May 2019, the National Development and Reform Commission issued the measures for the supervision and examination of transmission and distribution price costs, which stipulates that the cost of pumped storage can not be included in the transmission and distribution price fixing costs, that means grid companies will have to absorb the investment in pumped-storage plants themselves.

With the new round of electricity reform starting in 2015, the price control has been gradually released, but the fluctuation range is generally limited. At present, there are 8 spot markets in our country, whose declared or cleared prices are limited by fluctuation range. Some experts related to the power grid had an analysis of the "Caijing" reporter, if the government will limit the price fluctuations to 3 to 5 times, then the spot market for electricity is difficult to feed pumped storage.

However, under the pressure of the epidemic, the resumption of production has become a more important decision-making considerations. State Grid said in a news release that the construction of the pumped-storage hydroelectricity project in Shanxi was the State Grid Company's implementation of the Party Central Committee and the State Council's decision-making and deployment, and while doing its best to prevent and control the epidemic, we will carry out all tasks of reform, development and stability in a coordinated way, do a good job in the six stable tasks, promote the start of major projects and help enterprises resume work and production in an orderly manner.

In view of the future trend of increasing peak-to-peak power supply and demand gap and peak load, several power experts told Caijing that the market mechanism is the basis for ensuring all kinds of technological innovation. Whether it is pumped storage, electrochemical energy storage, demand side management and other new technologies, all need more market-oriented mechanism, through the price signal to guide the investment of new technologies.

The writer is a reporter for CAIJING

By Han Shulin
